1
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,961
HIERARCHY

2
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:25,668
You're crazy.

3
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:27,253
You're all crazy!

4
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:29,464
I have to…

5
00:01:29,547 --> 00:01:32,592
I… I'm gonna expose
everything that's going on here!

6
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:09,587
EPISODE 4

7
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:12,590
REVENGE, DESIRE, ROMANCE:
THE HEART OF THE MATTER

8
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,135
What about the guard?

9
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:18,346
I told him I left something behind.
That should buy us ten minutes.

10
00:02:26,104 --> 00:02:28,648
So, what exactly are you looking for?

11
00:02:28,731 --> 00:02:29,899
Drugs.

12
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:33,778
I saw Choi Yun-seok giving pills
to Kim Ri-an, who hid them in his locker.

13
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:37,949
Ms. Han said it's an antidepressant
like Xanax. I'm sure it's something else.

14
00:02:38,032 --> 00:02:39,701
I've heard about them
dealing drugs before.

15
00:02:39,784 --> 00:02:42,495
Weed, edibles, GHB, stuff like that.

16
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:48,126
Take a look.

17
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:05,393
Find anything?

18
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:09,606
What is it?
Is there something in those photos?

19
00:03:11,524 --> 00:03:12,734
I can't believe it.

20
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:16,487
I didn't know she could smile like that.

21
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:34,422
Oh, that's cold!

22
00:03:38,843 --> 00:03:40,803
Okay, you ready? Let's go.

23
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:44,974
No, wait!

24
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:26,349
It's so pretty.

25
00:04:26,975 --> 00:04:28,601
Just like you.

26
00:04:30,186 --> 00:04:31,104
Ri-an.

27
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:34,732
I'm so happy right now.

28
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:37,902
Usually, I'm so focused
on playing my role…

29
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:42,365
on how Jung Jae-i of the Jaeyul Group
should be acting.

30
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:45,118
It's almost etched into my brain.

31
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:49,914
With you, I don't worry about any of that.

32
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,543
I hear you.

33
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:56,713
It can feel good to forget who you are,

34
00:04:56,796 --> 00:05:00,091
to forget that I'm Kim Ri-an,
heir to the Jooshin empire.

35
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:07,265
I like feeling that way with you.

36
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:13,271
In fact,

37
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:17,900
I like you more than I thought
it was possible to like anyone.

38
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:54,187
I see you're on your way home.

39
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:57,440
We just landed, so I thought
I'd call you from the plane.

40
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:02,028
Well, Ri-an,
how did you feel about yesterday?

41
00:06:02,111 --> 00:06:03,988
How'd I feel about what?

42
00:06:04,072 --> 00:06:05,698
About the glimpse into your future.

43
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:08,701
The things that'll be yours,
the people you'll command.

44
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:10,745
Does it seem more real to you now?

45
00:06:10,828 --> 00:06:13,956
All this love I've prepared
for you to inherit one day?

46
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,042
You call that "love"?

47
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:17,126
You're right.

48
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:19,420
That kind of love can be a burden.

49
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:21,923
Jooshin Group's reputation,

50
00:06:22,006 --> 00:06:24,675
the future of its employees
and their families,

51
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,803
all of that will be on your shoulders.

52
00:06:26,886 --> 00:06:29,972
It's a heavy crown but a valuable one.

53
00:06:30,848 --> 00:06:33,601
You must protect your right
to inherit that crown, Ri-an.

54
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:36,104
Maintain your aura of nobility.

55
00:06:36,187 --> 00:06:38,398
Don't involve yourself
in any cheap scandals.

56
00:06:38,481 --> 00:06:39,565
Be above it.

57
00:06:40,274 --> 00:06:42,652
Always remind yourself
of how important you are.

58
00:06:43,444 --> 00:06:45,863
I'll talk to you again soon, my successor.

59
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:18,521
Your tutors are waiting.
Class will begin once you've changed.

60
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:20,481
Do I at least get a break?

61
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:23,860
You have strategic management with
Professor Cho of Seoul National University

62
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:26,612
and international trade
with Professor Son of Harvard.

63
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:29,615
Essential courses for a future leader
of a top company to master.

64
00:07:29,699 --> 00:07:32,618
These tutors were
meticulously chosen for you.

65
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:36,372
Besides, you have a commitment at
5:00 a.m. tomorrow. We can't reschedule.

66
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:37,665
I'm only 18.

67
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,042
I'm still just in high school.

68
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:43,212
My schedule is packed
from sunrise until after midnight.

69
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:47,592
I think I deserve some breathing room
when I get home from school, don't you?

70
00:07:47,675 --> 00:07:49,594
I understand that you must be tired,

71
00:07:50,094 --> 00:07:50,970
nonetheless…

72
00:08:01,063 --> 00:08:01,939
There you are.

73
00:08:02,023 --> 00:08:04,484
Oh, Woo-jin, sometimes your mom
doesn't have a clue.

74
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:08,196
If I'm trying to run for president,
I'll need Jooshin's heir to support me.

75
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:10,948
But all we have for him is
some measly seaweed soup?

76
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:12,992
I'll have you know Ri-an
specifically asked for it.

77
00:08:14,118 --> 00:08:16,621
Ri-an likes seaweed soup.
Thanks a lot, Mom.

78
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:19,957
-Ah, I think that's our cue to leave.
-Ah!

79
00:08:20,541 --> 00:08:22,502
Sometimes, your mom does have a clue.

80
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:24,921
-Please enjoy your meal, Ri-an.
-Thank you. I'm sure I will.

81
00:08:38,851 --> 00:08:40,311
It's just seaweed soup.

82
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,897
Why doesn't it taste like this
at my place?

83
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:45,024
You have the best chefs
in the world on your staff.

84
00:08:45,107 --> 00:08:47,902
-They can make anything you want them to.
-That's not true.

85
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:50,029
There are some things you can't fake.

86
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:53,824
The warmth of a home-cooked meal,
for example. Things like that.

87
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:56,661
You won't be getting that
at my place.

88
00:08:59,205 --> 00:09:00,206
Come over anytime.

89
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:03,709
-You'd help me be a good son.
-I know my parents would love it.

90
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:06,254
You're a good friend, man.

91
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:09,507
I really should come more often.

92
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:16,430
Something came to me recently.

93
00:09:17,932 --> 00:09:21,060
Being together felt so natural for us.
Jae-i and me.

94
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:23,729
Time we spent, she and I,

95
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:28,109
that was the only time
either of us felt anything like comfort.

96
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:32,822
I guess that's why
I've been feeling so anxious lately.

97
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:34,407
It's like a part of me is missing.

98
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:39,370
Can Jae-i really be okay with this?

99
00:09:39,453 --> 00:09:41,289
I know how anxious she gets.

100
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:44,292
No way.

101
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:46,252
I know she's hurting.

102
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:48,963
What about you?

103
00:09:51,173 --> 00:09:52,091
Let's eat.

104
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:58,556
Here.

105
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:12,862
Right before you pull the trigger,
the target senses it.

106
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:16,157
They can feel that a bullet
will soon be passing through their body.

107
00:10:16,907 --> 00:10:18,784
What matters next is how they react.

108
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:20,661
Either they stand clueless and meet death,

109
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:23,122
or they're swift enough
to live another day.

110
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:26,334
The look in their eyes at that moment,

111
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:29,337
in that brief instant
preceding their death or their escape,

112
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:32,381
is the most
exhilarating thing in the world.

113
00:10:32,965 --> 00:10:35,509
You're right. Every time
I hit something that's trying to run away,

114
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:38,012
I get this insane rush of adrenaline.

115
00:10:38,095 --> 00:10:39,930
That's why I find hunting enjoyable.

116
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,099
What about you, Jae-i?

117
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:47,605
Well, I think--

118
00:10:47,688 --> 00:10:50,358
"Oh, that poor thing,
so weak and defenseless."

119
00:10:50,941 --> 00:10:52,735
Something along those lines?

120
00:10:53,569 --> 00:10:55,613
Does that explain the scholarship boy?

121
00:11:00,242 --> 00:11:03,746
Do you feel the same compassion for him
as you do for the game animals

122
00:11:03,829 --> 00:11:06,666
that cower and flee from you
on the hunting grounds?

123
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:12,588
Because, otherwise,
I can't understand it.

124
00:11:13,255 --> 00:11:14,590
"Scholarship."

125
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:19,804
Well, I guess
it's like mother, like daughter.

126
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:23,766
Just something low-class sluts
have in common.

127
00:11:29,563 --> 00:11:31,232
Jae-hyeok?

128
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:33,359
Yeah, Dad?

129
00:11:35,444 --> 00:11:38,572
Don't ever let me hear you
talk like that again, you brat.

130
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:40,991
This isn't a subject for you
to babble about like an idiot.

131
00:11:46,622 --> 00:11:48,249
-Get out.
-Yes, sir.

132
00:11:55,798 --> 00:11:58,759
I felt sorry for him.
It was just like you said.

133
00:11:58,843 --> 00:12:01,804
I felt bad for him because
he was a scholarship student.

134
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:04,765
People at school exaggerated it.

135
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:06,684
I thought you'd learned your lesson.

136
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:08,477
You've seen first-hand

137
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:12,022
where trivial emotions like pity
can lead, haven't you? So why?

138
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:17,695
What happened
to the last kid wasn't enough?

139
00:12:27,913 --> 00:12:28,914
I'm sorry.

140
00:12:34,628 --> 00:12:36,213
You've spent enough time there.

141
00:12:37,965 --> 00:12:41,886
Thankfully, the rumors about Jooshin
and Jaeyul being enemies have died down.

142
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:44,597
You're moving to New York.

143
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,516
Start getting ready.

144
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:06,994
Noona.

145
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:13,042
That was annoying.

146
00:13:14,043 --> 00:13:15,503
Dad slapped me again,

147
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:18,088
and it's your fault.

148
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:20,800
I think he slapped you because
you don't know how to shut up.

149
00:13:21,425 --> 00:13:22,468
And by the way,

150
00:13:22,551 --> 00:13:24,637
don't call me "noona" ever again.

151
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:27,389
It makes my skin crawl.

152
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:29,225
What? Whoa!

153
00:13:30,017 --> 00:13:30,851
Does it?

154
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:34,730
"Skin crawl." Good one.

155
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:37,691
You sure seem confident, hmm?

156
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:40,611
Just remember,

157
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:44,198
noona…

158
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:50,704
that I still have cards I can play here.

159
00:13:52,748 --> 00:13:54,333
Don't forget what you signed.

160
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:22,111
Kim Ri-an!

161
00:14:23,571 --> 00:14:24,572
Let's go together.

162
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:28,242
-What do you want for lunch?
-Well done, Yoon He-ra.

163
00:14:28,325 --> 00:14:30,786
-You might survive this after all.
-What's that again?

164
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,080
Imagine if she tried
to take on Jae-i alone.

165
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:35,499
We'd be waving "bye"
at her funeral by now.

166
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:36,417
Mm-hmm.

167
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:38,878
By sticking next to Ri-an,
she has guaranteed protection.

168
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:40,421
Ah.

169
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:09,909
I asked you here to apologize.

170
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:11,160
My dad…

171
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:14,413
I'm sure you felt
insulted the other night.

172
00:15:15,789 --> 00:15:16,999
Meet Jae-i's boyfriend.

173
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,294
Nice to meet you, sir. Hi, I'm Kang Ha.

174
00:15:22,838 --> 00:15:26,467
What makes you think
you have the right to address me?

175
00:15:28,218 --> 00:15:31,221
Please don't worry about that.
It doesn't affect me at all.

176
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:34,934
I've had to put up with so much crap
here at Jooshin, I'm immune by now.

177
00:15:36,143 --> 00:15:37,061
But thanks anyway.

178
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:38,687
Why are you thanking me?

179
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,106
Plenty of people at this school
have done bad things to me,

180
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:43,192
but not one of them has apologized.

181
00:15:44,568 --> 00:15:46,612
You're the first person to do that, Jae-i.

182
00:15:51,158 --> 00:15:52,660
Well, if it happens again,

183
00:15:53,619 --> 00:15:56,330
don't wait around
expecting another apology.

184
00:15:56,413 --> 00:15:57,539
Don't try to fight.

185
00:15:58,499 --> 00:15:59,833
It's better to just run away.

186
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:03,379
Jae-i.

187
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:05,714
Do you still like Kim Ri-an?

188
00:16:08,425 --> 00:16:09,259
What?

189
00:16:09,343 --> 00:16:12,638
If you still do, can I ask what made you
break up with him and run away?

190
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:15,057
Did something force you to do it?

191
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,226
If you wanna be with him,

192
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:19,937
what's holding you back?

193
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:24,108
I thought I already told you.

194
00:16:25,442 --> 00:16:26,360
Remember?

195
00:16:27,069 --> 00:16:28,320
The line we don't cross?

196
00:16:38,372 --> 00:16:39,873
I wanna see your smiling face as well.

197
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:42,084
So how about it?

198
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:44,003
Let's date for real and stop faking.

199
00:16:45,629 --> 00:16:46,714
Forget Kim Ri-an.

200
00:16:47,589 --> 00:16:48,757
I'll be the one by your side.

201
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:54,221
You don't have to be
anxious or lonely anymore.

202
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:59,143
I'll make you smile. Or try, at least.

203
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:05,691
You don't have to be
anxious anymore.

204
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:09,445
I'm here to help.

205
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:11,572
Jae-i, I'll be by your side.

206
00:17:15,242 --> 00:17:16,285
It's strange.

207
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:18,495
They're so alike.

208
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:31,884
Who cares if it's real or fake.
It's all meaningless to me.

209
00:17:32,551 --> 00:17:34,887
-What do you mean?
-You could never understand.

210
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:37,347
-Why? Because I'm a scholarship student?
-No.

211
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:39,558
I don't think you and I are any different.

212
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:44,188
It's just, we both live
in completely different worlds.

213
00:17:44,897 --> 00:17:47,232
In my world, how I feel doesn't matter.

214
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:48,192
At all!

215
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:51,278
That's the world I have to survive in.

216
00:17:52,362 --> 00:17:54,364
At least until I can stand on my own.

217
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:57,659
What do you mean, "survive"?

218
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:59,411
I told you you wouldn't understand.

219
00:18:00,829 --> 00:18:03,082
I'm gonna pretend you never said that.

220
00:18:25,562 --> 00:18:26,772
Well, Ms. Park?

221
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:29,233
How do we look?

222
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:32,694
I will pretend I never saw you.

223
00:18:37,574 --> 00:18:38,867
Oh, and Ri-an?

224
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:44,456
Your mother was so gracious
to attend our school event the other day.

225
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:45,999
I hope I made that clear.

226
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:49,753
Would you pass on how truly thankful I am
for her doing us that honor?

227
00:18:49,837 --> 00:18:52,339
Tell her yourself like you always do.

228
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:55,300
Right.

229
00:19:00,305 --> 00:19:02,391
I can't tell who's in charge anymore.

230
00:19:03,058 --> 00:19:04,768
Whoever has the most power.

231
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:06,979
Huh?

232
00:19:13,735 --> 00:19:15,737
Age, gender,

233
00:19:16,363 --> 00:19:17,990
job title… none of it matters.

234
00:19:18,073 --> 00:19:20,701
These days, power is
the only thing that counts.

235
00:19:20,784 --> 00:19:22,452
You must have figured that out by now.

236
00:19:23,495 --> 00:19:24,997
Missed a button, Ms. Han.

237
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:31,879
Okay. Come to the lounge.

238
00:19:31,962 --> 00:19:33,005
Don't forget to eat lunch.

239
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:35,549
I'm meeting my friends.

240
00:19:37,092 --> 00:19:38,677
You don't really love me…

241
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:42,723
do you Woo-jin?

242
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:48,562
Jealous?

243
00:19:50,397 --> 00:19:51,398
But I'm not sure of who.

244
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:54,818
Or maybe…

245
00:19:56,987 --> 00:19:58,488
you're the one in love.

246
00:20:02,826 --> 00:20:03,660
Who is she?

247
00:20:04,369 --> 00:20:06,038
The woman in Lee Woo-jin's heart?

248
00:20:26,683 --> 00:20:27,726
I'll see you at the studio.

249
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,192
-Good afternoon.
-Hi, Ms. Han.

250
00:20:35,275 --> 00:20:36,235
Mm-hmm.

251
00:20:36,318 --> 00:20:37,945
Hey, did you see her bag?

252
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:40,489
-Yes, you are.
-Hello.

253
00:20:41,281 --> 00:20:44,409
-It's a secret.
-You are, right? Right? Right?

254
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:51,625
Jae-i?

255
00:20:54,336 --> 00:20:57,673
Normally, we apologize to someone
